cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Vox in your research or build on its design, please cite it."
type: software
title: "Vox: The AI-Native Programming Language"
abstract: >
  Vox is an AI-native, full-stack programming language that compiles to Rust (backend)
  and TypeScript (frontend). It is designed to minimize LLM hallucinations by providing
  a compiler-enforced, null-free type system where absence is Option[T] and failure is
  Result[T, E]. The language natively supports MCP (Model Context Protocol) tools,
  durable workflows, and actor-based concurrency as first-class language keywords.
authors:
  - family-names: "Brainerd"
    given-names: "Bert"
repository-code: "https://github.com/vox-foundation/vox"
url: "https://vox-lang.org"
license: Apache-2.0
version: "0.4"
date-released: "2026-04-01"
keywords:
